# Game Map Sizing

Tutorial levels use small rooms (42x16) for focused teaching. All later levels (Floor 1+) should use much larger rooms that fill most of the viewport.

- Target room size for gameplay levels: ~80x30 characters minimum
- The GameGrid should expand to fill available screen space between the HUD and MessageLog
- Room dimensions should be responsive — consider the player's viewport
- When designing room templates, use the full width/height to create interesting layouts
- Floor tiles, props, and enemies should be spread across the full area to avoid clustering

The renderer already supports arbitrary room sizes — just increase ROOM_W and ROOM_H in level data files.
